Document: AnimatedSprite3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedsprite3d.rst  
Summary: AnimatedSprite3D is a node that uses SpriteFrames resources to display animated textures in 3D scenes.  

AnimatedSprite3D is similar to the Sprite3D node, except it carries multiple textures as animation sprite_frames. Animations are created using a SpriteFrames resource, which allows you to import image files (or a folder containing said files) to provide the animation frames for the sprite. The SpriteFrames resource can be configured in the editor via the SpriteFrames bottom panel. AnimatedSprite3D inherits from Sprite3D and extends its functionality by enabling frame-based animations through the SpriteFrames resource. This resource manages the sequence of textures that make up the animation, allowing for smooth transitions between frames. The node does not render a single static texture but instead cycles through the frames defined in the SpriteFrames resource at a specified speed. Key Rule: The SpriteFrames resource must be assigned to the AnimatedSprite3D node for animations to play.
---CHUNK---
