Document: AnimatedSprite3D
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedsprite3d.rst
Summary: Methods for controlling animation playback, frame management, and state checks in AnimatedSprite3D.

Method: get_playing_speed() → float. Const method. Returns the current playback speed of the animation.
Method: is_playing() → bool. Const method. Checks if the animation is currently playing.
Method: pause() → void. Pauses the animation playback.
Method: play(name: StringName = "", custom_speed: float = 1.0, from_end: bool = false) → void. Starts playing the specified animation. If name is empty, uses the current animation. custom_speed scales playback speed. from_end starts playback from the end of the animation.
Method: play_backwards(name: StringName = "") → void. Plays the specified animation in reverse. If name is empty, uses the current animation.
Method: set_frame_and_progress(frame: int, progress: float) → void. Sets the current frame and progress within the animation. Frame is the index of the frame, progress is a value between 0 (start) and 1 (end) of the animation.
Method: stop() → void. Stops the animation playback and resets to the start frame.

Note: The animation_finished signal is not emitted if an animation is looping.
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimatedSprite3D
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedsprite3d.rst
Summary: Properties and methods for controlling animation playback and frame management in AnimatedSprite3D.

Property: animation (StringName) = "default"
Sets the current animation from the sprite_frames resource. Changing this resets the frame counter and frame_progress. Accessors: set_animation(value), get_animation()

Property: autoplay (String) = ""
Specifies the animation key to play when the scene loads. Accessors: set_autoplay(value), get_autoplay()

Property: frame (int) = 0
Displays the animation frame at the specified index. Setting this resets frame_progress. For direct frame/progress control, use set_frame_and_progress(). Accessors: set_frame(value), get_frame()

Property: frame_progress (float) = 0.0
Tracks progress between 0.0 (start of frame) and 1.0 (end of frame). Reverses direction (1.0 to 0.0) when animation plays backwards. Accessors: set_frame_progress(value), get_frame_progress()

Property: speed_scale (float) = 1.0
Controls animation speed scaling. 1.0 = normal speed, 0.5 = half speed, 2.0 = double speed. Negative values play animation in reverse. Zero stops animation. Accessors: set_speed_scale(value), get_speed_scale()

Property: sprite_frames (SpriteFrames)
References the SpriteFrames resource containing animations. Allows loading, editing, clearing, and saving SpriteFrames states. Accessors: set_sprite_frames(value), get_sprite_frames()
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimatedSprite3D
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedsprite3d.rst
Summary: Methods for controlling animation playback, speed, and state in AnimatedSprite3D.

get_playing_speed() → float
Returns the actual playing speed of current animation or 0 if not playing. This speed is the speed_scale property multiplied by custom_speed argument specified when calling play(). Returns a negative value if the current animation is playing backwards.

is_playing() → bool
Returns true if an animation is currently playing (even if speed_scale and/or custom_speed are 0).

pause()
Pauses the currently playing animation. The frame and frame_progress will be kept and calling play() or play_backwards() without arguments will resume the animation from the current playback position. See also stop().

play(name: StringName = "", custom_speed: float = 1.0, from_end: bool = false)
Plays the animation with key name. If custom_speed is negative and from_end is true, the animation will play backwards (equivalent to play_backwards()). If called with the same animation name or no name parameter, the assigned animation will resume playing if it was paused.

play_backwards(name: StringName = "")
Plays the animation with key name in reverse. This method is a shorthand for play() with custom_speed = -1.0 and from_end = true.

set_frame_and_progress(frame: int, progress: float)
Sets frame and frame_progress to the given values. Unlike setting frame, this method does not reset frame_progress to 0.0 implicitly.

GDScript:
    var current_frame = animated_sprite.get_frame()
    var current_progress = animated_sprite.get_frame_progress()
    animated_sprite.play("walk_another_skin")
    animated_sprite.set_frame_and_progress(current_frame, current_progress)

stop()
Stops the currently playing animation. The animation position is reset to 0 and the custom_speed is reset to 1.0. See also pause().